\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. O. patens} Desf.,{\i  Fl. Atl.}{\b  2}: 318 (1799) ({\i O. brevicornis} Viv.). Tubers ovoid. Stem 25-70 cm, erect, with a basal rosette or cluster of 3-5 leaves and with sheaths above. Leaves oblong ovate to lanceolate. Spike long-cylindrical. Bracts linear-lanceolate, 5- to 7-veined, c. ½ as long to as long as ovary. Flowers purple. Outer perianth-segments 8-10 mm, oblong, obtuse, greenish towards the base, the 2 lateral patent-deflexed, the median curved forward or erecto-patent; inner lanceolate-oblong. Labellum 9-10 mm, ovate, spotted, 3-lobed; lateral lobes obliquely oblong, truncate; middle lobe broadly obcordate, emarginate, with 2 truncate, crenulate lobules; base of labellum with 2 inconspicuous ridges. Spur saccate, directed downwards, shorter than labellum, c. ½ as long as ovary.{\i  W. Mediterranean region.} Bl Hs It Si.
